 It's a skill that anyone can hone, and one that benefits from thinking with others and over time. Breaking new ground in the discussion about how we innovate, this book provides strategies that everyone can use to be more creative.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aCreative ability in business. 0aCreative ability. 0aCreative thinking. 4acognition. 4acreativity. 4ainnovation. 4ainsight. 4ainvention. 4alearning. 4aproducts. 4askill. 4athinking. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Organizational Behavior.2bisacsh1 aLoewenstein, Jeffrey, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360551040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503605510423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503605510.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles